---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About | Nahor">
  <div style="max-width: 750px; margin: 80px auto; padding: 0 20px;">
    
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 40px; color: #1A1A1A; text-align: center;">
      About Nahor
    </h1>
    
    <div style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8; color: #444; text-align: justify;">
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
        Nahor is a digital magazine dedicated to thoughtful writing, visual arts, scientific inquiry, and cultural exploration. It was created as a space where ideas, creativity, and lived experiences can be shared with care, preserved with purpose, and discovered by readers across the world.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
        We believe that meaningful work deserves more than a fleeting place on social media or a forgotten PDF stored away in a folder. Nahor provides a lasting home for original poetry, essays, photography, artwork, travel narratives, and reflections that continue to inspire long after they are first published.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin: 50px 0 20px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eaeaea; padding-bottom: 10px; color: #0A3B2C; text-align: left;">
        Our Editorial Pillars
      </h2>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">The magazine is built upon four editorial pillars:</p>
      
      <ul style="margin-bottom: 30px; padding-left: 20px; text-align: left;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Canvas</strong> — Photography, paintings, digital art, illustrations, sketches, and mixed media.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Echoes</strong> — Poetry, short stories, reflective essays, memoirs, letters, translations, and flash fiction.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Interface</strong> — Science, technology, artificial intelligence, research stories, mathematics, philosophy of science, and scientific visualization.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Journeys</strong> — Travel writing, photo essays, nature writing, cultural exploration, and personal reflection.</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
        Alongside regularly published works, Nahor also releases curated <em>Issues</em>—thematic digital editions that bring together a collection of outstanding contributions centered around a shared idea or theme.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin: 50px 0 20px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eaeaea; padding-bottom: 10px; color: #0A3B2C; text-align: left;">
        Our Philosophy
      </h2>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
        Nahor values curiosity over trends, craftsmanship over speed, and timeless writing over momentary attention. We intentionally remain a non-political magazine, focusing instead on creativity, culture, science, technology, travel, and the shared human experience.
      </p>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
        Conceived and incubated by the Students' Society of Assam, Banaras Hindu University, Nahor is envisioned as an open digital platform that connects creative minds across disciplines, cultures, and geographical boundaries. We welcome submissions from students, alumni, faculty members, scientists, researchers, artists, photographers, writers, and curious minds from every background. Every submission undergoes editorial review to ensure that Nahor maintains its standards of originality, clarity, and quality while respecting the unique voice of each contributor.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
        Whether you are a reader discovering a new perspective, a photographer capturing a fleeting moment, a poet giving shape to an emotion, an artist expressing an idea, or a researcher translating complex concepts into accessible stories, Nahor invites you to become part of this growing archive of thoughtful work.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 50px; font-style: italic; color: #666;">
        As Nahor evolves, so will its community. We hope to welcome new contributors, editors, artists, and readers who believe that creativity, curiosity, and meaningful expression deserve a place that endures.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
